modules.description: This module manages an asynchronous terminal interface, handling input and output for interactive applications. It supports creating a terminal session with customizable options like mouse input and bracketed paste, rendering images, setting cursor positions, and responding to resize events. Typical use cases include building text-based user interfaces or interactive command-line tools that require real-time input and custom rendering.

This module provides asynchronous terminal input/output operations, including handling resize events, rendering images, and managing cursor positions. It works with terminal sessions configured with options like mouse support and bracketed paste. Concrete use cases include building interactive command-line applications and text-based interfaces requiring real-time user interaction and custom screen rendering.
